issue_body:
Hi,
I have the below module:
```yang
module g
{
    namespace "urn:g";
    prefix g;

    extension ac {
        argument "name";
    }

    container x
    {
      grouping test-grouping {        
        g:ac test {
              input {
                  leaf test {
                      type string;
                  }
              }
        }
      }

      uses test-grouping {
          augment "test/input" {
            leaf-list xyz {
              type int32;
            }
          }
       }
    }
}

```
Seeing the below error:
```
# pyang  g.yang 
g.yang:23: error: node g::test is not found
```

                container end
                {
                    tailf:cli-flatten-container;
    
                    leaf end_date
                    {
                        tailf:cli-drop-node-name;
                        tailf:cli-incomplete-command;
                        type xs:date; 
                    }
                    
                    leaf end_time
                    {
                        tailf:cli-drop-node-name;
                        type xs:time;
                        
                        must "compare(../end_date, ../../start/start_date) = 1 
                            or (compare(../end_date, ../../start/start_date) = 0 and compare(../end_time, ../../start/start_time) = 1) "
                        {
                           error-message "The end time can not less than start time!";
                        }

                    }
                }

when ./run.py -c config.json, raised the above error. The config.json as following：
{
  "webui": {
    "host": "192.168.1.32",
    "port": "5000"
  },
  "fetcher": {
    "xmlrpc": false
  },
  "scheduler": {
    "xmlrpc": false
  },
  "taskdb": "mysql+taskdb://root:*@myip:3306/db_taskdb",
  "projectdb": "mysql+projectdb://root:*@myip:3306/db_projectdb",
  "resultdb": "mysql+resultdb://root:*@myip:3306/db_resultdb",
  "amqp_url": "amqp://admin:*@myip:15672/%2F"
}
the os is ubuntu 14.04,  have been installed default RabbitMQ using apt-get install rabbitmq-server -y, what's the matter? thank you!

Looks like the arguments to `interpolate` are mixed up. Currently is:
```
def interpolate(x, y, new_x):
    if y.dtype.kind == 'f':
        return interp(x, y, new_x)
    else:
        idx = searchsorted(x, new_x, side='right')
        idx -= 1
        idx = clip(idx, 0, idx[-1])
        return x[idx]
```
Should be:
```
def interpolate(new_x, x, y):
    if y.dtype.kind == 'f':
        return interp(new_x, x, y)
    else:
        idx = searchsorted(x, new_x, side='right')
        idx -= 1
        idx = clip(idx, 0, idx[-1])
        return y[idx]
```
Because the function checks for the type of `y`, which is passed to the function as the current time channel and will always be a float, all channels are interpolated as floats, because the arguments to `interp` are also mixed up. But as it stands, no integer channels get the new `searchsorted` treatment.

@wjlutter reported this issue in #52. When reading data from a DAQmx data file, the data doesn't match what is obtained if the file is first converted to a normal TDMS file in LabView and then read in. It doesn't appear that this is related to scaling as reading the file without any scaling applied still results in incorrect data, and there isn't an obvious relation between the incorrect and correct data.

[daqmx_tdms_info.txt](https://github.com/adamreeve/npTDMS/files/1133694/daqmx_tdms_info.txt)
[converted_tdms_info.txt](https://github.com/adamreeve/npTDMS/files/1133695/converted_tdms_info.txt)

Trying following example fails with "pycparser.plyparser.ParseError: :3:32: before: __attribute__":

src = r"""
void testFunc(void) {
    extern int fooBarBuf[0x08] __attribute__ ((asection(".foo.bar","f=awB")));
} """

from pycparser import c_parser
p = c_parser.CParser()
ast = p.parse(src)
ast.show()

This was triggered by https://github.com/kennethreitz/maya/pull/150#issuecomment-388639920.

The [Travis file](https://github.com/kennethreitz/maya/blob/master/.travis.yml#L12) guided me to running the tests locally on my Mac. For some reason, I didn't investigate why, some of the tests fail.

Regardless of what the outcome is here I suggest to have the Travis CI build also run on macOS.

