In [o3dgcTimer.h#L33](https://github.com/assimp/assimp/blob/b5c7c9c/contrib/Open3DGC/o3dgcTimer.h#L33) there are some includes protected by an `#ifdef __MACH__`:

~~~C
#elif __MACH__
#include <mach/clock.h>
#include <mach/mach.h>
#else
#include <time.h>
#include <sys/time.h>
#endif
~~~

It seems that this is intended for OSX/macOS.
However there are other implementations of the *Mach Microkernel*, notably `GNU Hurd`, which lacks the `mach/clock.h` include.
Therefore this file cannot be built on the Hurd.

If the define was indeed meant for OSX/macOS, I suggest to use `__APPLE__` instead:
~~~C
#elif __APPLE__
#include <mach/clock.h>
#include <mach/mach.h>
#else
#include <time.h>
#include <sys/time.h>
#endif
~~~

